                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d119">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.41D112A/5: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Ireland</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dublin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-04-18T15:00:00+01:00"
                            >April 18, 1944—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 5 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>86. Department’s telegram 72, April 15, 5 p.m. Legation opinion expressed in
                    airgram A–44 August 16, 1943<note n="36" xml:id="d119fn36">Not printed.</note>
                    regarding extension of Proclaimed List to this country has not changed.
                    Desirability of inclusion in next month’s supplement is not, in our view,
                    affected by the situation resulting from the recent exchange of notes and no
                    objection is seen here to such inclusion.</p>
                <p>The Proclaimed List may include all names now on the Statutory List.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
